      "snippet": "Dear John Doe, We&#39;re thrilled to share that we have finalized the color schemes for your book titles! After carefully considering your preferences and ensuring alignment with your vision, the",
      "body": "Dear John Doe,\n\nWe’re thrilled to share that we have finalized the color schemes for your book titles! After carefully considering your preferences and ensuring alignment with your vision, the finalized designs are now ready. We believe these choices will make your titles stand out beautifully—both on retail shelves and in digital formats.\n\nHere’s a brief overview of the finalized color schemes:\n\n1. **“Title One”**: A rich combination of deep navy and brushed gold for a classic and sophisticated feel.\n2. **“Title Two”**: A vibrant teal paired with subtle coral accents to evoke energy and creativity.\n3. **“Title Three”**: Soft lavender with silver highlights for a calming, elegant touch.\n\nAs always, our priority is ensuring our designs reflect your brand and resonate with your audience. If there are any adjustments you’d like or additional feedback you wish to share, please don’t hesitate to reach out. \n\nWe appreciate your trust in Literary Horizons Design Studio, and we’re excited to see your titles in their final, polished form! \n\nLooking forward to hearing your thoughts.\n\nWarm regards,  \nColor Design Team  \nLiterary Horizons Design Studio  \nEmail: color.design@literaryhorizons.com\n"
    }
